# Sobelow Skipped Findings
# Format: "Fingerprint", "Type"
# Fingerprint is the first 14 characters of the SHA256 hash of the finding
# Type is the finding type (e.g., "Config.CSP", "XSS.Raw")
#
# Example:
# "abc123def45678", "Config.CSP"
#
# To add a finding to the skip list, run sobelow and copy the fingerprint:
#   mix sobelow --config --threshold low
# Then add entries here and re-run to verify they're skipped.
